<h3>Why does my Moorpark hillside home go through thermal fuses repeatedly?</h3>
<p>Almost certainly a long vent run that's out of LG specifications for your installation. Hillside homes in Campus Canyon, Mountain Meadows, and Peach Hill commonly have vent runs of 20+ feet — beyond what LG machines are designed to exhaust through efficiently. The machine heats but can't move air fast enough, temperature builds, fuse trips. We measure vent equivalent length on every Moorpark hillside call before making recommendations. If the run is within spec but restricted by lint — extended cleaning plus fuse replacement. If the run is out of spec — we give you the options for correction.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer in my Moorpark equestrian property shows d80 — could it be hay dust?</h3>
<p>Yes — equestrian properties in the Tierra Rejada Valley accumulate hay dust and animal particulate in exterior vent caps faster than standard residential areas. Compacted hay dust inside a cap housing doesn't clear with standard cleaning — we replace rather than clean on equestrian property calls where the cap is packed with particulate. Annual cap inspection recommended for any Moorpark property adjacent to equestrian use.</p>

<h3>My 1990s Moorpark home has never had the dryer vent cleaned — how urgent is this?</h3>
