<h3>Why do my LG dryer drum rollers wear out early in my Moorpark hillside home?</h3>
<p>Often an unlevel washer next to or under the dryer. On Moorpark's hillside lots in Peach Hill and Campus Canyon, a washer that's even slightly off-level vibrates hard during spin, and that vibration transfers to the dryer and wears the drum rollers and bearing faster than normal. Our LG Dryer Repair techs check washer leveling when roller wear looks premature, replace all four rollers, and the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

